titleInfo.title: Muhammad v. Bethel-Muhammad et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER entered re 5 Motion to Dismiss and 12 Motion to Dismiss. Motions are DENIED as MOOT, w/o prejudice to the movants' ability to file similar motions should the plaintiff file an amended complaint that withstands initial judicial scrutiny. The plaintiff's request for recusal, (Doc. 1 at 6, 98), is DENIED. The plaintiff's application for default, (Doc. 19), construed as a motion for entry of default, is DENIED. Plaintiff will be required to serve his amended complaint on defendant Bethel in accordance with Rule 4. Plaintiff is ORDERED to file and serve, on or before February 7, 2012, an amended complaint satisfying the pleading requirements set forth herein and in the Courts orders entered in Muhammad I. Failure to do so will result in dismissal of this action without prejudice, as further set out. Signed by Chief Judge William H. Steele on 1/24/2012. Copy of order mailed to Plaintiff (clr)
